h would have understood these overlapping challenges to be heralding a kairotic moment, reflecting simultaneous crises and opportunities. The collected essays reflect on the intersections of COVID and Kairos. Authors engage numerous ethical challenges precipitated by the current Kairos moment, thinking through and with Tillich. Other essays offer reflections on our cultural moment, engaging topics from public health to video games to hate speech. Reflecting on the cultural moment, this collection offers unique insight into the Tillichian legacy for the present and future.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Nov 2022) 4aCOVID-19 / Pandemie. 4aInternationale Krise. 4aKairos Moment. 4aTillich, Paul.  aCOVID-19.  aKairos moment.  aPaul Tillich.  ainternational crises.1 aChicka, Benjamin J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDanz, Christian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDanz, Christian, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDumas, Marc, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGrube, Dirk-Martin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMathot, Benoit, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRistiniemi, Jari, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRöbel, Marc, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchüßler, Werner, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchüßler, Werner, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSturm, Erdmann, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWagoner, Bryan, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aWichmann Kristensen, Anne-Milla, econtributor.4ctb